      "content": "While heat is the primary driver of the Maillard reaction, the type of sugar and other ingredients can influence its rate and intensity. For example, sucrose and glucose can contribute to a faster-browning reaction, while fructose and lactose can produce more caramel-like flavors. Additionally, the presence of amino acids, such as glutamine and asparagine, can accelerate the Maillard reaction. Some bakers also use ingredients like yeast, which can break down starches and release sugars, speeding up the reaction.",
